## Definition

+-- {: .un_defn}
###### Definition

A [[symmetric monoidal (âˆž,1)-category]] $(C,\otimes)$ is **closed** if for each [[object]] $X \in C$ the [[(âˆž,1)-functor]]

$$
  X \otimes (-) : C \to C
$$

givn by forming the [[tensor product]] with $C$ has a [[right adjoint|right]] [[adjoint (âˆž,1)-functor]]

$$
  (X \otimes(-)\dashv [X,-] ) : C \stackrel{\overset{X \otimes (-)}{\leftarrow}}{\underset{[X,-]}{\to}}
  \,.
$$

=--

## Examples

Every [[(âˆž,1)-topos]] with its structure of a [[cartesian monoidal (âˆž,1)-category]] is closed. See there for details.

